Jaiyeola Olukayode Two persons died in a helicopter that crashed at Opebi in Ikeja, Lagos on Friday. The National Emergency Management Agency, which made this known, also said one person was rescued. The crash occurred at No. 16, Salvation Road in Opebi, north of Lagos. The PUNCH had reported that the pilot was conveying two passengers to a destination in the state when the tragedy struck around 12.17 pm. See photos:  READ ALSO: Nigeria suffers 78% drop in Q2 foreign capital inflows 